<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1897-11-10T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1897-11-10T00:00:00-05:00" n="50" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d50">
                        <head><hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Conger</persName> to Mr.
                                    <persName type="to">Sherman</persName>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Legation of the United States</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Petropolis</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1897-11-10"><hi rend="italic">November 10,
                                    1897</hi></date>. (Received Dec. 7.)</dateline>
                            <seg rendition="#left">No. 57.]</seg></opener>
                        <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: Since writing my dispatch No. 56 of this
                            morning I have received a telegram from the President of Brazil, a copy
                            and translation of which I inclose.</p>
                        <p>I have, etc.,</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">E. H. Conger.</hi></signed></closer>
                        <frus:attachment>
                            <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Inclosure in No.
                                    57.—Translation.]</seg></opener>
                            <head><hi rend="italic">President <persName type="from">Moraes</persName> to Mr. <persName type="to">Conger</persName>.</hi></head>
                            <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName type="venue"><hi rend="smallcaps">Presidential Palace of the
                                            Republic</hi></placeName>,<lb/><date calendar="gregorian" when="1897-11-10"><hi rend="italic">November 10, 1897</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                            <p>Greatly obliged. I thank your excellency for the congratulations sent
                                me upon my providential escape, and for the expressions of sorrow on
                                account of the heroic death of the minister of war.</p>
                            <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Prudente
                                Moraes.</hi></signed></closer>
                        </frus:attachment>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>